38 //
39 // Defines the Dynamics class. Templated on the state type and control type,
40 // as well as the type of service response (SR) which encodes these dynamics.
41 //
43 
44 #ifndef FASTRACK_DYNAMICS_DYNAMICS_H
45 #define FASTRACK_DYNAMICS_DYNAMICS_H
46 
47 #include <fastrack/utils/types.h>
48 
49 namespace fastrack {
50 namespace dynamics {
51 
52 template<typename S, typename C, typename SR>
53 class Dynamics {
54 public:
55  // Destructor.
56  virtual ~Dynamics() {}
57 
58  // Initialize with control bounds.
59  void Initialize(const C& u_lower, const C& u_upper) {
60  u_lower_ = u_lower;
61  u_upper_ = u_upper;
62  initialized_ = true;
63  }
64 
65  // Derived classes must be able to give the time derivative of state
66  // as a function of current state and control.
67  virtual S Evaluate(const S& x, const C& u) const = 0;
68 
69  // Derived classes must be able to compute an optimal control given
70  // the gradient of the value function at the specified state.
71  virtual C OptimalControl(const S& x, const S& value_gradient) const = 0;
72 
73  // Get the min and max controls.
74  inline const C& MinControl() const { return u_lower_; }
75  inline const C& MaxControl() const { return u_upper_; }
76 
77  // Convert to the appropriate service response type.
78  virtual SR ToRos() const = 0;
79 
80  // Convert from the appropriate service response type.
81  virtual void FromRos(const SR& res) = 0;
82 
83 protected:
84  explicit Dynamics()
85  : initialized_(false) {}
86  explicit Dynamics(const C& u_lower, const C& u_upper)
87  : u_lower_(u_lower),
88  u_upper_(u_upper),
89  initialized_(true) {}
90 
91  // Lower and upper bounds for control variable.
92  C u_lower_;
93  C u_upper_;
94 
95  // Initialization.
96  bool initialized_;
97 }; //\class Dynamics
98 
99 } //\namespace dynamics
100 } //\namespace fastrack
